    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.206009>
    bibo:endPage "64" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "41" ;
    bibo:volume "2838" ;
    dc:creator "Vardo-Zalik, Anne M.; Campbell, Ronald A." ;
    dc:date "2011" ;
    dc:title "Five new species of Acanthobothrium van Beneden, 1849 (Cestoda: Tetraphyllidea) in elasmobranchs from the northwest Atlantic and Gulf of Mexico with first records from smooth-hound sharks and guitarfish" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.206015>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.206016>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.206012> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.206015>
    dc:description "FIGURES 25 – 30. Acanthobothrium westi sp. nov. from Raja texana. 25. Scolex, note rounded bothridia joined by velum and length of cephalic peduncle. 26. Hooks, note form of lateral hook (left). 27. Hooks, note form of lateral hook (right). 28. Bothridium, note bothridial form and position of septa. 29. Terminal (mature) segment. 30. Detail of ovary. Note overlap of left lobe over right lobe posteriorly. Scale bars: Figs. 25, 29 = 100 um. Figs. 26, 27 = 35 um. Figs. 28, 30 = 50 um." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/206015/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.206016>
    dc:description "FIGURES 31 – 36. New Acanthobothrium species from Gulf of Mexico. 31. A. ulmeri sp. nov., holotype. 32. A. westi sp. nov., holotype. 33. A. westi sp. nov., scolex from specimen 2.24 mm long. 34. A. ulmeri sp. nov., scolex from specimen 1.2 mm long. 35. A. schalli sp. nov. detail of hooks showing elongated tubercles. 36. A. schalli sp. nov., holotype, entire worm with 18 segments. Scale bars: Figs. 31, 32 = 250 µm, Figs. 33, 34, 35 = 50 µm, Fig. 36. = 500 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/206016/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.206012>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9 – 13. Acanthobothrium lentiginosum sp. nov. from the Atlantic guitarfish. 9. Scolex. 10. Hooks. 11. Mature segment. Note posterior extent of testes. 12. Detail of bilobed ovary, inverted A-shaped. 13. Entire worm. Scale bars: Figs. 9, 11, 13 = 100 µm. Figs. 10, 12 = 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/206012/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

